{
  "case_id": "D2N092",
  "method": "cap",
  "template": "soap",
  "summary_text": "S:\nThe patient reports pain in his arm, specifically tenderness over the distal radius following a tennis injury. He describes pain when pressing on the arm and when flexing his thumb, but less pain with passive range of motion. He also reports some numbness in his hand and pain when moving his wrist. He reports a history of allergies and takes flonase. He sustained an injury to his arm while playing tennis and reports a fall while using a rake.\n\nO:\nPhysical exam reveals tenderness to palpation over the distal radius. Range of motion is limited due to pain. Neurological exam is unremarkable. The x-ray shows no fractures or abnormalities.\n\nA:\nThe primary problem is a strain and contusion of the muscle in the distal radius. There is no fracture.\n\nP:\nI am ordering motrin 800 milligrams three times a day with food. If the pain does not improve in one week, we will schedule a follow-up to assess the situation further.",
  "reference_summary": "CC:\n\nRight arm pain.\n\nHPI:\n\nMs. Martinez is a 43-year-old female who presents today for an evaluation of right arm pain after she hitting her arm on a pole while playing tennis. She had mild swelling at the time. There is pain with motion. She denies any numbness or tingling in her hand. She has a past medical history of allergies and takes Flonase.\n\nEXAM\n\nExamination of the left wrist shows tenderness over the distal radius and pain with flexion of the wrist and thumb.\n\nRESULTS\n\nX-rays of the left wrist show no obvious signs of acute fracture or other abnormality.\n\nIMPRESSION\n\nRight wrist sprain.\n\nPLAN\n\nAt this point, I discussed the diagnosis and treatment options with the patient. I have recommended ice and anti-inflammatory medications. I am prescribing Motrin, 800 mg to take 3 times a day with food. She will follow up with me in 1 week or as needed.",
